Inputs\: keyName - the key to check Responses\: isNull - if the key is a null pointer. notNull - if some value is stored in the key. 62a7b953-6fc0-4913-9a63-c3c04f955282.1c10dbba-a247-4d92-a861-e5924558138b.transition.description=No good URLs were found. 62a7b953-6fc0-4913-9a63-c3c04f955282.1d7e44bd-eec9-4311-83bd-cfe8919a7303.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);

62a7b953-6fc0-4913-9a63-c3c04f955282.7c05cfda-c475-4193-807c-1a583503df3e.description=Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way. Inputs\: notifydata - The message to notify the user of. notifyMethod - The method of notification (file, email, display). subject - This is a description of what the notification is about. destination - for files, the file to write to, for emails the email to send to. notificationServer - If the specified method send the notifyData to a server, this is the name of the server to notify (i.e. an email server) from - This is the originator of the message (email from address). sourceServer - Some integrations use a multi-level server architecture for processin tickets, this is the name of a mid-tier server in such an architecture. serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. username - A username to use when authenticating to a notification method requireing authentication. password - The password for username. Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. 62a7b953-6fc0-4913-9a63-c3c04f955282.7c084462-431b-4c65-9fca-37e3d8da37bc.description=
Crawls through a set of URLs starting from a URL (or list of URLs) provided as input. The flow visits the web pages in the baseURL input and, if it is allowed (recursionDepth > 0), will also visit in a recursive manner the URLs that are referred (in hyperlinks) by the previously visited pages. This process repeats upto a certain level of recursion specified using the recursionDepth input - this prevents the flow from crawling endlessly. The flow will only test a URL a single time. The tested URLs are classified by the flow as good, slow or bad and passed in the corresponding results.

Inputs\:
    baseURL - The list of URLs to be tested. Semicolon (;) is used as delimiter for this list.
    recurse - Specifies whether the crawler will recurse. If set to "Yes" it will recurse to a depth specified by the recursionDepth numeric input. If set to "No" the crawler will not recurse regardless of the recursionDepth input.
Valid values\: Yes, No.
Default value\: No.
    recursionDepth - The depth to which the crawler will continue to test linked pages.
Default value\: no recursion limit - this means that the crawler is allowed to recurse endlessly if the recurse input is "Yes".
Valid values\: natural numbers.    
    timeout - How many milliseconds a page is given to respond before it is considered slow.
Default value\: 0 - this means that there is no response timeout and a page is considered "good" if it responds successfully.
    allowedDomains - A semicolon delimited list of domains that the flow is allowed to crawl through. This does not need to include the domain of baseURL.
    username - The username to use for authentication to the URLs.
    password - The password to use for basic authentication to the URLs.
    proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the URLs.
    proxyPort - A port on the proxy to connect to.
    proxyUsername - A username to use when connecting to the proxy.
    proxyPassword - A password to use when connecting to the proxy.
    followRedirects - Specifies whether or not the "get" command should automatically follow redirects.
Default value\: false.
    trustAllRoots - Enables weak security over SSL. An SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted CA issued it.
Default value\: false.
    trustKeystore - URL of the truststore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS server authentication is not to be used.
    trustPassword - Password to unlock the truststore.
    characterSet - The characterSet for HTTP Get request and response.
Default value\: UTF-8.
    keystore - URL of the keystore file or local path to it (e.g. %JAVA_HOME%/jre/lib/security/cacerts). It may be empty if HTTPS client  authentication is not to be used.
    keystorePassword - Password to unlock the keystore.
    authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server. 
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
    useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value. 
Default value\: true.
    userAgent - If the HTTP header USER_AGENT needs to be overridden, pass in the value here.
    kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
    headerNamesList - A list containing the names of headers that should be used for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list containing the values of headers that should be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list containing the names of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - A list containing the values of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - A delimiter that separates the elements in the names and values lists.
Default value\: , (comma).

Responses\:
    success - The web pages were tested and classified.
    failure - The web pages could not be tested and classified.

Results\:
    badURLs - A semicolon delimited list of URLs that did not respond, or responded with an HTTP error.
    slowURLs - A semicolon delimited List of URLs that took longer than timeout milliseconds to respond. This result will be empty if timeout input is 0.
    goodURLs - A semicolon delimited List of URLs that were tested successfully and before the timeout expired.
    toTest - A list of all the URLs that were tested.
    errorMessage - If an error occurred, an informational message that may help determine the cause of the error.

Note\:
1. If you need to specify query parameters when making the request, consider using the “queryNamesList” and “queryValuesList” inputs. The operation also accepts including query parameters in the url (Example\: http\://hostname\:80/page.asp?parameterName1\=parameterValue1¶meterName2\=parameterValue2). If you specify the same query parameter both through the "queryNamesList" and through the url input, then the value from the "queryValuesList" list will be used and not the one included in the url.
2. Currently, the only supported application server when using form-based authentication is Apache Tomcat.

This flow checks every link on a specific web page.

Inputs\:
    notifyMethod - How the user should be given the results of the flow.
    baseURL - This is the url to check
    recurse - Specifies whether the crawler will recurse. If set to "Yes" it will recurse to a depth specified by the recursionDepth numeric input. If set to "No" the crawler will not recurse regardless of the recursionDepth input.
Valid values\: Yes, No.
Default value\: No.
    recursionDepth - The depth to which the crawler will continue to test linked pages.
Default value\: no recursion limit - this means that the crawler is allowed to recurse endlessly if the recurse input is "Yes".
Valid values\: natural numbers.
    timeout - How many milliseconds a page is given to respond before it is considered slow.
Default value\: 0 - this means that there is no response timeout and a page is considered "good" if it responds successfully.
    allowedDomains - A semicolon delimited list of domains that the flow is allowed to crawl through. This does not need to include the domain of baseURL.
    username - The username to use for authentication to the URLs.
    password - The password to use for basic authentication to the URLs.
    proxy - A proxy to use when accessing the URLs.
    proxyPort - A port on the proxy to connect to.
    proxyUsername - A username to use when connecting to the proxy.
    proxyPassword - A password to use when connecting to the proxy.    
    followRedirects - Specifies whether or not the "get" command should automatically follow redirects.
Default value\: false.
    trustAllRoots - Specifies whether to enable weak security over SSL. A SSL certificate is trusted even if no trusted certification authority issued it.
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: true
    keystore - The location of the KeyStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS client authentication is used. The default value will be provided if trustAllRoots is false.
Default\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    keystorePassword - The password associated with the KeyStore file. If trustAllRoots is false and keystore is empty, keystorePassword default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    trustKeystore - The location of the TrustStore file - a URL or the local path to it. This input is empty if no HTTPS server authentication is used. The default value will be provided if trustAllRoots is false.
Default\: /java/lib/security/cacerts
    trustPassword - The password associated with the TrustStore file.  If trustAllRoots is false and trustKeystore is empty, trustPassword default will be supplied.
Default value\: changeit
    authType - The authentication type that this operation uses when trying to execute the request on the target server. 
Valid values\: basic, form, digest, ntlm, kerberos, anonymous (no authentication).
    useCookies - Enables cookie tracking. Cookies will be stored between consecutive calls. This is a boolean input. If a non-boolean value is specified, it will take the default value. 
Default value\: true.
    userAgent - If the HTTP header USER_AGENT needs to be overridden, pass in the value here.
    kerberosConfFile - The path to the Kerberos configuration file. If this input is empty the kdc (Key Distribution Center) and realm will get their values from the full domain name which is obtained from the url of the web server.
    headerNamesList - A list containing the names of headers that should be used for the request.
Example\: Accept,Content-Type
    headerValuesList - A list containing the values of headers that should be used for the request. 
Example\: text/plain,application/x-www-form-urlencoded
    queryNamesList - A list containing the names of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterName1,parameterName2 
    queryValuesList - A list containing the values of query parameters that should be used for the request. 
Example\: parameterValue1,parameterValue2
    delimiter - A delimiter that separates the elements in the names and values lists.
Default value\: , (comma).

Responses\:
    success - The flow succeeded, no bad links were found.
    failure - The flow failed.
    diagnosed - Some bad links were found.

Note\:
1. If you need to specify query parameters when making the request, consider using the “queryNamesList” and “queryValuesList” inputs. The operation also accepts including query parameters in the url (Example\: http\://hostname\:80/page.asp?parameterName1\=parameterValue1¶meterName2\=parameterValue2). If you specify the same query parameter both through the "queryNamesList" and through the url input, then the value from the "queryValuesList" list will be used and not the one included in the url.
2. Currently, the only supported application server when using form-based authentication is Apache Tomcat.
